Definition.WordDefinition: Unusual \Un*u"su*al\, a. Not usual; uncommon; rare; as, an unusual season; a person of unusual grace or erudition. -- {Un*u"su*al*ly}, adv. -- {Un*u"su*al*ness}, n. [1913 Webster]
unusually adv : to a remarkably degree or extent; "she was unusually tall" [syn: {remarkably}, {outstandingly}, {unco}] [ant: {normally}]
